5000.Name: Wavecat Pillow
5000.Desc: The seventh product of the smash hit Momo Friends collaboration line-up! This Wavecat-shaped pillow is this year's third most popular bedding item.

5001.Name: Peroro Wheel
5001.Desc: The ninth product of the smash hit Momo Friends collaboration line-up. This Peroro-shaped exercise wheel is this year's most popular fitness accessory!

5002.Name: A-Pods Pro
5002.Desc: Wireless earphones that are all the rage among Kivotos students. A bit expensive to buy on a tight budget, since they retail for about three months worth of part-time pay.

5003.Name: Forbidden Love: Its Beauty Lies in its Illicitness
5003.Desc: The latest work from the popular romance novelist who wrote "Koi About Love"! Delve into a dizzying tale of forbidden love!

5004.Name: Hitgirls Gaming Magazine
5004.Desc: Stay up to date on the latest releases, strategies for classic games, new gaming merch and everything in between—this magazine covers it all!

5005.Name: Cherry-Rose Lip Gloss
5005.Desc: A lip gloss with a subtle yet striking hue. It's one of the hottest selling items among young ladies interested in beauty products.

5006.Name: Glassy Glow BB Cream
5006.Desc: A hit product from the luxury cosmetics brand Samuela. This BB cream evens out skin tone and provides a natural finish for a healthy glow.

5007.Name: Military Camo Foundation Trio
5007.Desc: A hit product from the luxury cosmetics brand Samuela. It provides lightweight camouflage capabilities that melt into your skin! Be camera-ready any time, any place!

5008.Name: Fine Cookie Set
5008.Desc: A luxury cookie set from Schrodinger, famed for its rich, buttery sweetness. There's a fifty percent chance that it contains something other than cookies.

5009.Name: Guns, Charm, and Zeal
5009.Desc: Guns, charm, and zeal! The bestselling book of the year investigates and analyzes the origins and roots of Kivotos pop culture.

5010.Name: Astronomical Telescope
5010.Desc: This astronomical telescope is deemed the standard for hobbyists by the Kivotos Astronomy Observatory.

5011.Name: Gamegirl Color Replica
5011.Desc: "Life is your arcade!" Go retromania wild with this vintage reproduction of the classic Gamegirl Color.

5013.Name: Matcha Ramune
5013.Desc: A matcha-flavored, carbonated soft drink. Green and refreshing!

5014.Name: Jellies Cushion
5014.Desc: The star of "Fruitjellies" is back! In cushion form! They've managed to recreate the concept of a jelly eating another jelly of the same color in great detail!

5015.Name: Extraordinary Cottontail Detective:- Case of the Misty Hot Spring Slide -
5015.Desc: Whenever there's a case, these snow-white bunny ears are sure to crack it! Volume 3 of the Extraordinary Cottontail Detective series! The stage is set at the hot springs!

5016.Name: Ring Bit
5016.Desc: "Make fitness fun with games!" This exercise equipment uses an O-ring to make working out at home easy and fun whether for strength training or slimming down!

5017.Name: Buried Treasure Map
5017.Desc: There's treasure out there somewhere! A map of the sites where the three great gold treasures of Kivotos are supposed to be buried.

5018.Name: Cosplayer Coke-Bottle Glasses
5018.Desc: Wear these to instantly look like a genius! Einstein's got nothing on you (in appearance, anyway)! ※ Note: Wearing these will not raise your IQ.

5019.Name: World's Most Useless Gadget
5019.Desc: Absolutely useless, but cute! Still, it's completely pointless. And yet, its cuteness totally makes up for it! This trinket is among the top five best toys to give to a special friend.

5020.Name: Teddy Bear with Bow
5020.Desc: An ordinary but absolutely darling teddy bear. A popular product among students who love all things cute and adorable.

5021.Name: Movie Ticket
5021.Desc: "Snuggle up with your special someone and watch a movie!" This movie ticket is accepted at any theater and admits two people!

5022.Name: 30-Color Paint Set
5022.Desc: A professional paint set with tubes in a variety of thirty colors. Time to go and paint the whole wide world!

5023.Name: Classical Poetry Anthology
5023.Desc: An anthology of classical poetry. Very classy. Provides all the sophistication of classical literature right at your fingertips.

5024.Name: Cute Dishware Set
5024.Desc: A dishware set painted with adorable animal characters. This product has made the top ten list of best selling dishware in Kivotos year after year.

5025.Name: Brain Teaser Puzzle Cube
5025.Desc: "If you can solve this, then you deserve your place at Millennium!" A tricky cube for advanced puzzle-solvers certified by Millennium Science School.

5026.Name: Large Whole Cake
5026.Desc: The mere sight of this massive cake is enough to satisfy the senses. Its caloric info is detailed underneath.

5027.Name: Luxury Buffet Ticket
5027.Desc: This ticket grants access to a luxury buffet operated by the best chef in all of Kivotos. As you might expect, it's very expensive.

5028.Name: Potted Bug-Eating Plant
5028.Desc: A potted plant that's popular among those with eccentric taste. Apparently, the way it devours insects is cuter than you'd think.

5029.Name: Extravagant Gilded Jar of Greed
5029.Desc: An obviously exorbitant-looking jar gilt with gold leaf. Watch out for counterfeits!

5030.Name: Wind-Up Music Box
5030.Desc: A fancy solid wood music box with vintage charm. Very popular among collectors.

5032.Name: Encyclopedia
5032.Desc: From "that tie thing" for tying bread bags to "the grass thing" that goes in bento boxes, everything you've ever wanted to learn about can be found right here.

5033.Name: Health Food Supplement
5033.Desc: Feel rejuvenated with just one bite! This supplement is the perfect gift for your special someone.

5034.Name: Summer Floaty
5034.Desc: It's summer! To the beach! A safety device for swimmers of all experience levels. It'll have you ready for anything with its cute and fancy design!

5100.Name: Lace Pillow
5100.Desc: A lace pillow made of luxurious materials. It looks simple at first glance, but it's a classic design the students love and helps them drift off into sweet dreams.

5101.Name: Streets of Thugs Vol. 1
5101.Desc: Volume 1 of the Streets of Thugs series, a controversial work famous for the line, "All we have is loyalty and guts!" The series is getting favorable reviews because the main character is surprisingly cute, which you wouldn't guess from the title.

5102.Name: Samuela "The Beyond"
5102.Desc: A high-end perfume released by the luxury cosmetics brand, Samuela. It's an ultra-hit product famous for its catchphrase, "Spray it once, be lovely forever." It's one of Samuela's twelve masterpieces created by genius perfumer, The Beyond.

5103.Name: Antique Egg Handicraft
5103.Desc: An egg-shaped handicraft with beautiful jewels and geometric patterns. Of course, incubating it won't hatch chicks.

5104.Name: Mille-Feuille Traditional Parfait
5104.Desc: A parfait sold at the Mille-Feuille Cafe, a famous confectionery shop in Trinity. The harmony of sweets with layers of soft serve ice cream, syrup, whipped cream, and fruit is a classic hit!

5105.Name: Airbook Rare
5105.Desc: A trendy laptop product that's one of the students' top three most-wanted items of the year. The expensive price tag doesn't seem to stop anyone.

5106.Name: Sophisticated Hairbrush
5106.Desc: A portable hairbrush with a sophisticated, luxurious design. It's a popular gift.

5107.Name: Nutrient-Packed Multivitamin Gummies
5107.Desc: Multivitamin gummies. They're fun to eat with their various fruit flavors. You might end up finishing the entire bottle without even realizing, so be careful!

5108.Name: Finest Maple Bonsai
5108.Desc: A maple bonsai that calms your mind just by looking at it. The ever-changing appearance of the leaves according to the four seasons gives off a profound energy.

5109.Name: Sewing Kit
5109.Desc: A sewing kit for advanced users that contains tools meant for all possible situations. Even if your clothes or socks get holes, you can patch it up in a jiffy with this kit!

5110.Name: Music Concert Ticket
5110.Desc: A ticket for concerts held regularly in Kivotos. From the classics to contemporary pop music, it's the perfect gift for anyone who loves a wide variety of music.

5111.Name: Three Times a Day Dumbbell Set
5111.Desc: A set containing several dumbbells of various weights. Use them three times a day, morning, noon, and evening, for strength training to build great muscles!

5112.Name: Board Game "The Life"
5112.Desc: A fun board game where you can get a job, win the lottery, and travel to space. The unpredictable results of the wheel and dice work just like real life.

5996.Name: Refreshing Bouquet
5996.Desc: A bouquet made of amethysts to give to a loved one. The luxurious petals glow elegantly.

5997.Name: Beautiful Bouquet
5997.Desc: A bouquet made of rubies to give to a loved one. The beautiful red petals will capture the recipient's heart.

5998.Name: Hatsune Miku Photo Card
5998.Desc: A special photo card distributed at Miku's Kivotos Live Concert. They have become rare pieces of merch that any Miku fan wants to own.

5999.Name: Shiny Bouquet
5999.Desc: This crystal bouquet is the perfect gift for a special someone. It sparkles like a kaleidoscope in the light.

9998.Name: Secret Tech Sheet
9998.Desc:
A sheet fragment of Tech Notes with secret tech recorded on it.
Create a Secret Tech Sheet via Material Fusion with collected pieces.

10030.Name: Chinatsu (Hot Spring)'s Eleph
10030.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Chinatsu (Hot Spring).

10031.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Aru (New Year).

10080.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Shokuhou Misaki.

10100.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Shiroko Terror.

16010.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Hibiki (Cheer Squad).

16012.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Junko (New Year).

20007.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Hatsune Miku.

20009.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Cherino (Hot Spring).

20010.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Nodoka (Hot Spring).

20011.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Serika (New Year).

20025.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Haruka (New Year).

20031.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Shigure (Hot Spring).

20034.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Akari (New Year).

26011.Name: Saten Ruiko's Eleph
26011.Desc: The mystical Eleph of Saten Ruiko.

80000.Name: Event Points
80000.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80001.Name: Kitsune Senbei
80001.Desc: The iconic street food of Hyakkiyako's festivals. Each crispy bite is full of melt-in-your-mouth deliciousness!

80002.Name: Tanuki Okonomiyaki
80002.Desc: It's not a Hyakkiyako festival without this beloved treat! The raccoon drawn in mayo is adorable.

80003.Name: Sakura Daifuku
80003.Desc: The steadiest-selling dessert of Hyakkiyako's Momoyodou tea house. Its subtle yet rich sweetness makes it a classic.

80010.Name: Cherino Matryoshka
80010.Desc: A matryoshka made in Cherino's majestic likeness. Something rattles inside when you shake it.

80011.Name: Cherenka Chocolate
80011.Desc: An affordable milk chocolate made by the Red Winter School Lunch Club. It's sweet and soft, but Red Winter students find it difficult to eat when hardened by the cold.

80012.Name: Mustache Crepe
80012.Desc: A sweet and soft crepe sold throughout Red Winter Academy. Also known as a blini. Cherino's approval is required to add the mustache-shaped cream decoration.

80013.Name: Red Mustache Medal
80013.Desc: A luxurious gold medal with precious stones awarded to students Cherino recognizes as worthy. Most keep it stored in their desks due to its sharp edges.

80020.Name: Event Points
80020.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80022.Name: Beach Shack Meal Ticket
80022.Desc: A shabby meal ticket that can be used at the Beach Shack.

80023.Name: Weird Fireworks
80023.Desc: Has the shape of a cute missile.

80024.Name: Ice Cooler
80024.Desc: An ice cooler that can store fruit and drinks at a cool temperature. It's also effective at storing temperature-sensitive firearms.

80025.Name: Sand Play Set
80025.Desc: A Sand Play Set with tools for building simple sandcastles. Cement and rebar not included.

80026.Name: Beach Chair
80026.Desc: A modern beach chair with soft fabric laid atop wood. It's waterproof, allowing you to use it with ease at the beach.

80027.Name: Parasol Table
80027.Desc: A solid wood table with a sunshade parasol. A proper lady can't miss tea time, even at the beach.

80028.Name: Water Play Equipment
80028.Desc: Full-fledged watersports equipment with a snorkel and oxygen tank. Not recommend for depths exceeding 50m.

80029.Name: Sailing Board
80029.Desc: A board with sails attached to the hull to increase acceleration. It's easy to balance, making it perfect for beginners.

80030.Name: Gehenna Supply Box
80030.Desc:
Supplies prepared by the Prefect Team before summer boot camp.
They'll help you train! Don't worry, they're all winners!

80031.Name: GRS Grilled Corn
80031.Desc:
Grilled corn prepared by the Gourmet Research Society.
Curated to the tastes of its members—tastiness not guaranteed!

80032.Name: Thug Summer Shades
80032.Desc:
Seized by the Prefect Team from a troublemaker at the beach.
Signs of a helpless struggle remain.

80033.Name: Splashy Helmet
80033.Desc:
Seized by the Prefect Team from a Splashy Helmet Gang hoodlum in the beachside slums.
Signs of a futile struggle remain.

80040.Name: Event Points
80040.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80041.Name: Turtle Mushroom
80041.Desc: An exotic mushroom that grows naturally throughout the Shanhaijing district. Contrary to how it looks, its firm texture and great taste make it a delicacy.

80042.Name: Black Bamboo Shoot
80042.Desc: Black bamboo shoots growing in the gardens of Genryumon. Difficult to obtain due to strict management of Genryumon officers.

80043.Name: Ginseng Doll
80043.Desc: A human-shaped root herb found deep in the mountains of Shanhaijing. It's said to have effects that prolong your life or make you younger.

80050.Name: Chocolate Coin
80050.Desc: One of the famous snacks of the Golden Fleece. Not a real coin, but popular among students because of its sweet taste.

80051.Name: Rabbit Sticker
80051.Desc: A rabbit-shaped sticker used by students. They don't really mean anything. They're easy to make, so most students make their own.

80052.Name: Boarding Pass
80052.Desc: A boarding pass for the Golden Fleece. Even after boarding, it is best to carry it at all times since it's often needed functions and events.

80053.Name: Dice
80053.Desc: Dice like those often found aboard ships. Although they're a simple toy, they are sometimes used to resolve conflicts between students.

80060.Name: Event Points
80060.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80061.Name: Hot Spring Towel
80061.Desc: Basic towels provided by Hot Springs Resort No. 227. They're made from rough materials and may cause damage to the skin.

80062.Name: Mustache Shampoo
80062.Desc: President Cherino's favorite Red Winter Academy special shampoo. Contrary to the name, it's not suitable for washing a mustache.

80063.Name: Capybara Bath Bomb
80063.Desc: A bath bomb in the shape of a capybara. When you put it in water, it melts and gives off a subtle citrus scent.

80070.Name: New Year's Lucky Pouch
80070.Desc: A lucky pouch prepared by the Kurokame Gang for New Year's. No one knows what's inside until they open it up. There's actually some pretty good stuff in there.

80071.Name: Peroro Kagami Mochi
80071.Desc: Kagami mochi made in collaboration with the super popular mascot, Peroro, by the money-hungry Kurokame Gang. For decoration only and cannot be eaten.

80072.Name: Kurokame Gang Ema
80072.Desc: Ema sold at the Kurokame Gang's New Year's event. There's a rumor that its effect will increase if you give an offering and make a wish. That's why they're overpriced at 5,000 yen each.

80073.Name: New Year Omikuji Token
80073.Desc: Token required to pick out a New Year's omikuji. Something the Kurokame Gang created to increase profits. Prizes are awarded according to the results of the fortune-telling.

80080.Name: Event Points
80080.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80081.Name: Baddie's Apology Letter
80081.Desc: An apology letter written by troublemakers that Sensei caught while on Valentine's Day patrol. Surprisingly, the letter is nicely written.

80082.Name: Confiscated Junk Food
80082.Desc: Snacks confiscated from troublemakers during a Valentine's Day patrol. They're said to be black-market products made within underground circles. The junk food taste is popular among troublemakers.

80083.Name: Eco-Friendly Trash Bags
80083.Desc: Bags of trash collected from various places while on Valentine's Day patrol. Beautification activities are always rewarding.

80084.Name: Valentine's Day Outing Pass
80084.Desc:
An outing pass needed for any sensei who is busy with Valentine's Day patrol tasks but wishes to meet with students.
※ Unused outing passes will be converted to 200,000 credits at the end of the event.

80090.Name: Wakamo Arrest Warrant
80090.Desc: A warrant issued by Valkyrie Police School to arrest Wakamo. It states all of the terrible crimes that Wakamo has committed.

80100.Name: Event Points
80100.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80101.Name: Missal Veil
80101.Desc: A folded veil used while praying. It's also useful for covering up sleepy faces during prayers.

80102.Name: Hymn Book
80102.Desc: A book of Trinity's hymns. Certain verses occasionally become popular and are quoted incessantly or used in advertisements.

80103.Name: Cathedral Candle
80103.Desc: A candle used in the Trinity Cathedral. Despite its appearance, it's very heavy and sturdy, and can make a hole in the ground if dropped.

80110.Name: Mushiqueen Card Pack
80110.Desc: The Ultimate Insect Collection, third expansion pack of the popular trading card game, Mushiqueen. According to Kaede, you can tell whether it contains a rare card just by touching it.

80111.Name: Scrimmage Flyer
80111.Desc: A flyer announcing the exchange meeting held between Hyakkiyako and Gehenna Academy. The meeting's schedule is printed on it, along with a greeting from Niya, the promoter.

80112.Name: Princess Waraku Fan
80112.Desc: A fan with a drawing of Chise, a popular student at Allied Hyakkiyako Academy. It's a very popular item among her fans.

80113.Name: Ninpero Plush Merch
80113.Desc: Ninja character merch sold at the Whirlpool Movie Village. It started as a spin-off of another character, but it slowly gained popularity and became an independent product, which is common in the industry.

80120.Name: Materials Box
80120.Desc: Boxes of materials have been dumped all over the abandoned resort. They've been there for a long time, so it's unknown what's inside.

80130.Name: Local Currency
80130.Desc: The local currency of the Lost Paradise Resort, which was created for the purpose of revitalizing tourism. It's unknown if it's really legitimate, but Shizuko says it's only a matter of time before she can prove it.

80131.Name: Momoyodou Shiny Coin
80131.Desc: Coins that can be exchanged for souvenirs at the Momoyodou Beach Shack. However, most of the customers seem to think of the coin itself as a souvenir.

80132.Name: Shiny Conch
80132.Desc: A conch with a smooth and silky exterior. Chise says that if you put it to your ear and listen, you'll be naturally inspired to write poetry.

80133.Name: Summer Ninjutsu Codex Scroll
80133.Desc: A scroll with various original ninjutsus that can be used in summer. There are many writings related to summer safety. Safety comes first, even for ninjas!

80134.Name: Deep Sea Hot Springs Island Resort Ticket
80134.Desc: Resort agreement that gives the holder the right to use the Deep Sea Hot Springs Island Resort.

80135.Name: Mushiqueen Cruise Resort Ticket
80135.Desc: Resort agreement that gives the holder right to use the Mushiqueen Cruise Resort.

80136.Name: Ultra Luxury Resort Ticket
80136.Desc: Resort agreement that gives the holder right to use the Ultra Luxury Resort.

80140.Name: Dessert Coupon
80140.Desc: A coupon issued at a famous dessert shop. Collect and take them to the shop. There's a specific dessert that can be acquired with a certain number of coupons.

80141.Name: Mint Chocolate Parfait
80141.Desc: A mint chocolate parfait with a unique taste. It's fresh and sweet at the same time.

80142.Name: Macaron
80142.Desc: Macarons that fit in the palm of your hand. There are so many different flavors!

80143.Name: Rolled Wafer
80143.Desc: A chocolate-flavored snack that's rolled up into a long, hollow piece. Some students put it in their mouth and shake it to look cool.

80150.Name: Event Points
80150.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80151.Name: Beanbag
80151.Desc: A soft cloth pouch filled with beans and sand. It's light enough that there's no risk of hurting anyone, so it's frequently used in throwing competitions. In a few rare cases, explosive beanbags have been discovered.

80152.Name: Millennium Flag
80152.Desc: A small flag that displays Millennium's emblem. It's commonly used to designate a gathering place for students.

80153.Name: Whistle
80153.Desc: No ordinary whistle, this device features advanced technology from the Engineering Department. The vibrations caused by blowing into it trigger an electrical signal, which activates a speaker. It plays a recording of a bird chirp.

80160.Name: Sports Drink
80160.Desc: A sports drink developed at Millennium. Thanks to large amounts of data collected by the Athletic Training Club, drinking this drink will hydrate you faster than any others.

80161.Name: Relay Baton
80161.Desc: A baton used in relays. Don't worry; while it looks like an old stick hand grenade, it's actually been retrofitted with an electrical sensor that prevents it from exploding. As long as it's handed off to the next runner in time, that is.

80162.Name: Red Bean Bun
80162.Desc: A simple bun filled with red bean paste. It's been wrapped in plastic for the bread eating competition. While simple, these buns are extremely popular among some students from Valkyrie Police School.

80163.Name: Information Brochure
80163.Desc: A brochure handed out by the Kivotos Halo Festival Headquarters. It contains a complete game schedule, and even shows popular restaurants near the stadium.

80170.Name: Christmas Gift
80170.Desc: Everyone is counting down the days until Christmas! Better be good, or you won't get presents...

80171.Name: Christmas Stocking
80171.Desc: A stocking, hung with the hopes it will be filled with presents. In a pinch, you could wear it to keep your feet warm.

80172.Name: Candy Cane
80172.Desc: Red-and-white candy shaped like a cane. It smells like peppermint.

80173.Name: Eggnog
80173.Desc: A hot drink made with milk, eggs, and sugar. It's sure to warm you up on even the coldest day.

80180.Name: Event Points
80180.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80181.Name: Red and White Fish Cakes
80181.Desc: Fish cakes in two colors, white and red. The red color is said to represent auspiciousness and joy, while the white color represents sanctity.

80182.Name: Snapper
80182.Desc: A fish that is a necessity for an osechi meal, paired with shrimp. Celebrate New Year's right with some delicious snapper!

80183.Name: Omikuji Exchange Ticket
80183.Desc: Everyone says that it's just for fun, but it still feels a bit ominous when you get a bad one...

80200.Name: Multi-Dimensional Computational Unit
80200.Desc: A piece of a computational device from the Ark of Atrahasis. The circuits that make it up are incomprehensibly complicated.

80201.Name: Dimension Engine Part
80201.Desc: A piece of the Dimension Engine. On its own, it's a simple piece of machinery and doesn't seem very useful.

80202.Name: Space Choco-Burger
80202.Desc: A choco-burger that was vacuum-packed to use as a space ration. Exactly why something like that might be found here is up for debate even now.

80203.Name: Gate Unlock Code - Outer District 2
80203.Desc: A chip where the code to open the Outer District 2 gate is stored.

80204.Name: Gate Unlock Code - Outer District 3
80204.Desc: A chip where the code to open the Outer District 3 gate is stored.

80205.Name: Gate Unlock Code - Central District
80205.Desc: A chip where the code to open the Central District gate is stored.

80220.Name: Event Points
80220.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80221.Name: Student Council Hard Hat
80221.Desc: A hard hat printed with the logo of the General Student Council. It was made specially for the recovery effort.

80222.Name: Financial Report
80222.Desc: A financial report prepared by the Treasurer's Office, a division of the General Student Council's Board of Administration. It thoroughly details the financial status of Kivotos.

80223.Name: Pollock Roe Crackers
80223.Desc: Momoka's favorite snack. The salty flavor makes your mouth water.

80230.Name: Immaculate Maid Hairband
80230.Desc: Keeping a clean headband is all a part of a competent maid's job!

80231.Name: Makeup Palette
80231.Desc: This makeup palette might seem basic, but with a skilled enough hand it can create any disguise.

80232.Name: Old Mansion Invitation
80232.Desc: An invitation to the old mansion. There have been rumors of supernatural occurrences at this historic site...

80240.Name: Card Bundle
80240.Desc: A bundle of game cards popular in Shanhaijing. The more you collect, the more games you can play.

80241.Name: Black Tortoise Promenade Meal Ticket
80241.Desc: A meal ticket issued by the Black Tortoise Promenade. Take it with you to receive the hospitality of the Black Tortoise Promenade.

80242.Name: Genryumon Badge
80242.Desc: A badge with a drawing of the Genryumon. It's sold as one of their merch but isn't very popular...

80243.Name: Solvent Extraction Set
80243.Desc: A solvent extraction set they say can be used by anyone. Rumor is the Plum Blossom Garden is particularly reluctant to purchase it.

80250.Name: High-Quality Fountain Pen
80250.Desc: A high-quality fountain pen used by the General Student Council to sign documents. The ink flows smoothly, reducing hand and wrist fatigue.

80260.Name: Frozen Shrimp
80260.Desc: Shrimp that's been frozen immediately after being caught to preserve freshness. These frozen shrimp are a specialty of the Yatoura Village, who supplies most of the shrimp shipped to the D.U.

80261.Name: Pebble
80261.Desc: A small pebble often found on the beach. It looks ordinary, but the distinctively smooth and shiny surface is a result of years of exposure to the waves.

80262.Name: Seashell
80262.Desc: A small seashell commonly found on the beach. While all seashells may look similar at first glance, take a closer look. You'll notice subtle differences in the patterns.

80263.Name: Dried Starfish
80263.Desc: A starfish that's been left out on the dock to dry out. It can't be eaten and doesn't decay easily, so they are considered a nuisance by the villagers. Still, Miyu seems to feel a strange sense of kinship to it.

80265.Name: Guaranteed Roll (1) Ticket
80265.Desc: This ticket guarantees the results of a dice roll in Dice Race. This ticket will disappear when you choose 1 as your Guaranteed Roll.

80266.Name: Guaranteed Roll (2) Ticket
80266.Desc: This ticket guarantees the results of a dice roll in Dice Race. This ticket will disappear when you choose 2 as your Guaranteed Roll.

80267.Name: Guaranteed Roll (3) Ticket
80267.Desc: This ticket guarantees the results of a dice roll in Dice Race. This ticket will disappear when you choose 3 as your Guaranteed Roll.

80268.Name: Guaranteed Roll (4) Ticket
80268.Desc: This ticket guarantees the results of a dice roll in Dice Race. This ticket will disappear when you choose 4 as your Guaranteed Roll.

80269.Name: Guaranteed Roll (5) Ticket
80269.Desc: This ticket guarantees the results of a dice roll in Dice Race. This ticket will disappear when you choose 5 as your Guaranteed Roll.

80270.Name: Guaranteed Roll (6) Ticket
80270.Desc: This ticket guarantees the results of a dice roll in Dice Race. This ticket will disappear when you choose 6 as your Guaranteed Roll.

80290.Name: Event Points
80290.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80291.Name: Parchment Fragment
80291.Desc: A fragment of old parchment. It looks like you might be able to put it back together if you collect enough.

80292.Name: Lemon
80292.Desc: The fruit of the lemon trees that grow all over the island.

80293.Name: Old Key
80293.Desc: An old, simple key of a common design. Probably goes to a chest or cabinet somewhere.

80300.Name: Tarot del Luna
80300.Desc: A tarot card created for fans of a particular genre. Collect enough and you might be able to play a game.

80301.Name: Ink Cartridge
80301.Desc: Consume this to acquire ink. Try not to spill, as the ink is hard to wash out.

80302.Name: Tablet Pen
80302.Desc: It feels exactly like using pen and paper...according to the ad copy.

80303.Name: Official Con Ticket
80303.Desc: This ticket grants entry to the exhibition. Be careful not to lose it and watch out for forgeries.

80310.Name: Event Points
80310.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80311.Name: Train Ticket
80311.Desc: A train ticket. You only need the one.

80312.Name: Document Bag
80312.Desc: This document bag keeps its contents safe. But there may be more than documents in here...

80313.Name: Train Crew Whistle
80313.Desc: A train crew whistle. Perfect for shattering the peace of everyone around you.

80330.Name: Machine Part
80330.Desc: A part used to repair equipment and facilities in the Millennium Ruins. They can be found throughout the Ruins and can be collected to make equipment work.

80331.Name: Unusual Screw
80331.Desc: A screw with a rather unusual shape. Used by devices in the Millennium Ruins.

80332.Name: Weird Wire
80332.Desc: A weird wire that can only be found in the Millennium Ruins. It is in good condition.

80333.Name: Unverified Data Chip
80333.Desc: A chip containing data on the equipment in the Millennium Ruins. Contains a variety of files.

80350.Name: Financial Calculator
80350.Desc: A special calculator the General Student Council issued to the Treasurer's Office for finances. It's equipped with various features and can calculate complex formulas.

80360.Name: Event Points
80360.Desc: These points are earned from progressing in an event. Earn more points to trade in for a large variety of rewards.

80361.Name: Superalloy Camping Pack
80361.Desc: A sturdy iron rod used to secure a tarp or tent. It's made from a superalloy specially designed by Millennium Academy, so it doesn't rust or break easily.

80362.Name: Multipurpose Rope
80362.Desc: A highly elastic rope that can serve many purposes. It's made of special materials developed by Millennium Academy, so it's unbelievably strong. It could probably even tie down a tank.

80363.Name: S&D Curry Powder
80363.Desc: Curry powder sold by S&D, a well-known spice company. The unique spiciness pairs perfectly with curry, as well as many other cuisines.

80380.Name: Event Points
80380.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80381.Name: Premium Cocktail Glass
80381.Desc: A cocktail glass filled with sweet grape juice. It's designed to be able to easily swirl its contents in a very elegant fashion.

80382.Name: Table Napkin
80382.Desc: A table napkin beautifully decorated with purple flowers. Place it gently on your lap before enjoying a meal to avoid staining your clothes.

80390.Name: Target Clue
80390.Desc: Clue about the targeted subject. Crucial for progressing with the task.

80391.Name: Concert Program
80391.Desc: The program for the concert. While it's an excellent souvenir, the riveting live performance can only truly be experienced in-person.

80392.Name: Bow Tie
80392.Desc: A small bow tie often worn in upscale venues. Designed for convenient and comfortable use by anyone.

80393.Name: Opera Binoculars
80393.Desc: Binoculars to allow for a clear view of the stage no matter where you are in the venue. Elevate your viewing experience if you weren't lucky enough to get front row seats!

80394.Name: Valentine's Day Outing Pass
80394.Desc:
Use this pass to meet with students in between your Valentine's Day patrol tasks.
※ Unused passes will be converted to 400,000 credits after the event ends.

80400.Name: Hyakkiyako Commemorative Card
80400.Desc: Souvenir playing card often found at tourist locations. Collect enough of them to play some games!

80401.Name: Field Trip Itinerary
80401.Desc: A document outlining the schedule for a field trip. It's important to organize thoroughly, even if things don't always go to plan.

80402.Name: Guide Flag
80402.Desc: A guide flag to lead tourists. Especially helpful for keeping a group of wandering students together.

80403.Name: Special Coupon Book
80403.Desc: A book containing various coupons that can be redeemed at tourist attractions. Spending wisely on a trip is essential.

80420.Name: D-Day Calendar
80420.Desc: A countdown calendar to the day of the final battle. Time waits for no one!

80421.Name: Recharge Cookie
80421.Desc: A cookie to recover depleted HP. It won't truly satisfy your hunger.

80422.Name: Motivation Boost Candy
80422.Desc: A candy that revives your lost motivation. The flavor is random.

80423.Name: Event Points
80423.Desc: These points are earned each time you progress in an event. The more you earn, the greater the variety of rewards you can receive.

80440.Name: Water Park Wristband
80440.Desc: A wristband provided to water park guests. It allows access to lockers, and can be used for purchases.

80441.Name: Safety Whistle
80441.Desc: A whistle for signaling emergencies. When blown hard, it produces a loud, piercing sound.

80442.Name: Lifebuoy
80442.Desc: A lifebuoy used to rescue someone in the water. Make sure to connect the rope before throwing it.

80443.Name: Life Vest
80443.Desc: A life vest that helps you stay afloat in water. Make sure to wear one that fits securely.

80450.Name: ゲームコーナー利用券
80450.Desc: ゲームコーナーに入場できる入場チケット。デザインだけでも挑戦欲求を刺激する。

80451.Name: ヘルメット団総連合会記念コイン
80451.Desc: ヘルメット団総連合会を記念して発行された記念コイン。海辺での思い出を振り返ることができる。

80452.Name: 屋台メニュー表
80452.Desc: 海辺の屋台に備えられたメニュー表。おいしい食べ物でいっぱいだが、お金の使い過ぎには注意しよう。

80453.Name: 大会用水鉄砲
80453.Desc: ヘルメット団の水鉄砲大会のために用意された水鉄砲。水の代わりに弾丸が出るが、とにかく名前は水鉄砲だ。

80460.Name: お土産の人形
80460.Desc: あるお偉いさん……の形をとって作られた、交流会限定の人形。欲しがる生徒が多いせいか、回収率が意外と低い模様……

80461.Name: 小型のお茶セット
80461.Desc: 山海経の特産品の一つであるお茶セット。お茶の楽しみ方は自由だが、山海経ではそれぞれの拘りがある模様……

80462.Name: 六和閣模型
80462.Desc: 玄龍門曰く、山海経の真髄をイメージした記念品。飾っておけば、それなりの趣があるかもしれない。

80463.Name: 幸運のキーホルダー
80463.Desc: 提灯の形に作られたキーホルダー。幸運を願う気持ちが込められている。

80470.Name: 月影祭の商品券
80470.Desc: 月影祭でのみ使用できる期間限定の商品券。たくさん集めれば、「あるゲーム」に挑戦できるようだ。

80471.Name: 月影祭の月餅
80471.Desc: 祭りの成功と豊饒を祈願する月影祭の月餅。普通の月餅よりも小さく、食べやすい一口サイズになっているのが特徴だ。

80472.Name: 錬丹術研究会の特製栄養剤
80472.Desc: 祭りの成功のために、錬丹術研究会が特別に調剤した栄養剤。気力を高める効果があるらしい。

80473.Name: 月影祭の爆竹
80473.Desc: 祭りには欠かせない爆竹。安全に使えるよう十分考慮されて作られているが、万が一の事故には気をつけよう。

80490.Name: イベントPt
80490.Desc: イベントで入手できるポイント。たくさん手に入れることで、様々な報酬を獲得することができる。

80491.Name: ライブチケット
80491.Desc: 多くのユニットが参加する学園祭ライブの入場チケット。ライブの後は、大切な参戦記録として取っておこう。

80492.Name: カラフルペンライト
80492.Desc: ライブの主役と共に輝く、カラーチェンジ可能なペンライト。広い会場でも、これがあればアイドルとファンは一つになれる。

80493.Name: ぷちケーキ
80493.Desc: 学園祭の各所で配られるケーキ。一部の人にとっては学園祭に訪れる理由になるほど、味は絶品。

80500.Name: 謎の物質
80500.Desc: 現地で収集した謎の物質。特定の「再分析」を行うと、全く異なる結果物が得られるらしい。

80520.Name: 妖怪MAX梅干し味
80520.Desc: 筆舌に尽くしがたい「妖怪MAX」。マニア曰く、口の中に残る梅干しの香りがたまらないらしい。

80521.Name: ふかふか枕
80521.Desc: 柔らかさと弾力のバランスが絶妙な枕。頭を乗せた次の瞬間には、朝になっていると評判。

80522.Name: 新弾カードパック
80522.Desc: コユキが先生と遊ぶために用意したカードパック。レアカードを狙うには箱買い必須だ。

80523.Name: BOOM：クラシックコレクション
80523.Desc:
マキがみんなと遊ぶために持ち込んだ、あらゆる機器にインストールできる傑作ゲーム。
倒しても倒してもBOOM！

180000.Name: Chocolate Potato Chips
180000.Desc: Potato chips coated with chocolate on one side. The sweetness of chocolate complements the crunchy texture of the chips, but it doesn't seem like Momoka cares for them.

180001.Name: Angel Chocolate
180001.Desc: PB chocolate from the convenience store chain Angel 24. Sora accidentally placed a large order, but with Sensei's help, she succeeded in selling it all.

180002.Name: Bulk Mini Chocolates
180002.Desc: Mini chocolates that Rin bought in bulk and left in the reception room to eat while working. Just normal mini chocolates with nothing special about them.

180003.Name: Arona's Chocolate Ginger Cookies
180003.Desc: Chocolate ginger cookies that Arona baked. Sensei and Arona are depicted with white chocolate on top of the cookies.

180004.Name: Peroro Valentine
180004.Desc: Peroro-shaped chocolate sold on Valentine's Day. It's very popular among fans because it's a limited seasonal product.

180005.Name: Ration D-Type
180005.Desc: Military chocolate made from oats and cocoa powder. It's high in calories, making it suitable for long-term missions.

180006.Name: Happy Hot Chocolate
180006.Desc: Hot chocolate that Hanae makes. With one sip, your fatigue melts away and you feel happy.

180007.Name: Schokolade Gehenna
180007.Desc: A high-calorie, high-caffeine dark chocolate made at Gehenna. People often mistake it for a can of shoe polish since it is packaged in a round can.

180008.Name: Bulk Chocolate
180008.Desc: Chocolate that Akari bought in bulk to prepare for the chocolate eating contest. Gives ordinary people stomachaches by simply looking at it.

180009.Name: Chocolate Dango
180009.Desc: Dango dipped in chocolate sold at a famous traditional candy store. The harmony of flavors tastes surprisingly great.

180010.Name: Death Love
180010.Desc: A free gift that comes with the purchase of Black Death Poison's limited edition Valentine's album, "Love Is Conquered by Pulling Out the Heart". It's soft and sweet despite how spooky it looks.

180011.Name: Rider's Snack
180011.Desc: An energy bar that Shiroko always carries when cycling. The energy bar is full of chocolate-coated nuts that give you energy as soon as you take a bite.

180012.Name: Chocolate Ocean Friend
180012.Desc: Whale-shaped chocolate sold as a souvenir at the Maritime Museum. It's much larger than the other chocolate fish.

180013.Name: Desert Rose
180013.Desc: Rose-shaped chocolate sold at the Abydos station. They're based on desert rose stones and make for a popular gift.

180014.Name: Venus' Chocolate
180014.Desc: Risque chocolates for adults. They don't seem to be very popular due to their explicit shape.

180015.Name: Wiretapping Device No. 14
180015.Desc: A wiretapping device made by Kotama to look like chocolate. It doesn't seem like she wants it to be discreet.

180016.Name: Hot Cocoa Can
180016.Desc: A chocolate-flavored canned drink mainly sold in vending machines. The heat from the can helps warm the body.

180017.Name: Chocolate Pave Set (Receipt Inc.)
180017.Desc: A chocolate gift set that Yuuka bought for Sensei. Although it's premium chocolate that costs over 10,000 yen, it comes with a receipt stating it costs 5,000 yen for some reason.

180018.Name: Hero Chocolate (Item)
180018.Desc: A limited-time chocolate item from the RPG that Yuzu plays with Sensei. It slightly recovers the player's HP when eaten.

180019.Name: Homemade Chocolate Slime
180019.Desc: A homemade chocolate item by Aris based on a slime monster from a game. Its appearance leaves much to be desired.

180020.Name: Chocolate Frenzy MAX
180020.Desc: A chocolate-flavored Frenzy MAX sold for the Valentine's Day season. It tastes nasty, but it has an excellent energizing effect.

180021.Name: Chocolate Spray
180021.Desc: A spray that dispenses chocolate instead of ink. It can be used to sweeten up the world according to Maki.

180022.Name: Chocolate Shell Mk.2
180022.Desc: A chocolate shell developed by Hibiki for Valentine's Day. It creates a huge chocolate swamp wherever it hits when fired.

180023.Name: Chocolate Screw
180023.Desc: Chocolate made in the shape of a screw and covered in silver foil. It cannot be used as a tool despite its striking resemblance to a real screw.

180024.Name: Cherenka
180024.Desc: Red Winter Academy's special milk chocolate produced by the Red Winter School Lunch Club. Cherino has already taken a bite of it.

180025.Name: Improved Cherenka
180025.Desc: An improved version of the standard Cherenka with a cute illustration drawn by Tomoe. It tastes almost exactly the same as original Cherenka.

180026.Name: Cacao Bean
180026.Desc: A cacao bean that Nodoka barely managed to afford and intended to give to Sensei as a gift. It's not sweet, but it has a good flavor when brewed like tea.

180027.Name: Immortality Elixir (Failure)
180027.Desc: A new elixir made by Saya with chocolate as the base. A mistake during development resulted in a plain chocolate-flavored drink instead of an actual elixir.

180028.Name: Rum Bonbons
180028.Desc: Elegantly-scented chocolate bonbons with rum. They are a bit mature for students to eat.

180029.Name: Chocolate Cuffs
180029.Desc: Chocolate made in the shape of handcuffs. They're wrapped up in silver foil and look pretty real, but obviously don't work as actual handcuffs.

180030.Name: Special Chocolate Cruller
180030.Desc: Master Donuts' special chocolate cruller only sold during Valentine's Day season. The special sprinkles add more sweetness.

180031.Name: Chocolate Haniwa
180031.Desc: Haniwa-shaped chocolate prepared by Hanako. It's a bit creepy.

180032.Name: Little Bullet
180032.Desc: Chocolate from Hasumi in the shape of a sniper rifle bullet. It may be small in size, but it's amazingly sweet.

180033.Name: Hina's Homemade Chocolate
180033.Desc: Chocolate from Hina made by courageously overcoming her shyness. It doesn't look pretty, but the heart that went into making it is more beautiful than anything else.

180034.Name: A Relaxing Bite
180034.Desc: Chocolate made with ingredients carefully selected by Ako. She purposefully made chocolate that can be consumed habitually, just as good secretaries approach their work.

180035.Name: Delicious Chocolate! Really!
180035.Desc: Chocolate made from ingredients that Izumi thinks are the best for chocolate. Delicious according to Izumi. It is especially salty and savory.

180036.Name: Boss' Finest Chocolate
180036.Desc: The finest chocolate, purchased online by Aru to show appreciation for Sensei's work as her business partner...though, it's actually quite common. Still, it's the thought that counts.

180037.Name: Roulette from Hell
180037.Desc: Prank chocolate that lit up Mutsuki's eyes when she found it online. The unlucky winner gets a taste of hell. It's the perfect product for pranking friends.

180038.Name: Mug of Hot Cocoa
180038.Desc: Hot cocoa that Fuuka made for Sensei. It's warm and sentimental, and you can feel Fuuka's sweet kindness emanate from it.

180039.Name: Gave-It-All Chocolate
180039.Desc: Homemade chocolate for Sensei that Juri gave everything she had to make. Taste aside, Juri's sincerity can be felt just by looking at it.

180040.Name: Our Time Together
180040.Desc: The finest chocolate cake that Serika received from a part-time job she worked with Sensei. The taste of the sweet and fluffy cake is mixed with the taste of the sweat they'd shed together working.

180041.Name: Chocolate Gift Set
180041.Desc: A gift set of chocolate candies bought at a department store with Sensei. It makes for the best Valentine's Day gift because it contains an assortment of candy that one never tires of.

180042.Name: The Final Choice
180042.Desc: The best product that Sumire found after testing 100 different exercise supplements for Sensei. You'll feel full for the entire day after just one serving.

180043.Name: Advance! Upalupa Chocolate
180043.Desc: Chocolate with a toy that Momoi pulled from a crane game. A mascot character from the popular fighting game "The Fist of Cassiopeia - Upalupa Great Battle" is included. There are seven types in total.

180044.Name: Midori's Homemade Chocolate
180044.Desc: Homemade chocolate that Midori woke up early to make for Sensei. Wanting to be the first person to give chocolate to Sensei, her heart was warm and puffed up with anticipation while making it.

180045.Name: Chocolate Tsujiura Senbei
180045.Desc: Slightly strange chocolate crackers prepared by Chise that contain various idioms. Most of the content is normal, but on rare occasions, you may get one with something absurd written on it.

180046.Name: Momoyodou Limited Dessert
180046.Desc: A limited-edition dessert sold by Momoyodou in celebration of Valentine's Day. It is a special item that reflects the preferences of a certain regular customer. In other words, it's mostly made for Sensei.

180047.Name: Chocolate Ninja Set No. 49!
180047.Desc: A set of various chocolate must-have ninja tools. Izuna wanted to taste it with her lord and managed to get by standing in line early in the morning. Note: Cannot actually be used as tools.

180048.Name: Chocolate Sleep Kit
180048.Desc: A sleeping kit for Valentine's Day prepared specifically by Tsubaki for Sensei, who is always tired from overtime work. It costs 3,980 yen in total.

180049.Name: Wakamo's Love Chocolate
180049.Desc: Homemade chocolate made with Wakamo's overflowing, uncontrollable love. However, it is uncertain if love really is the only thing it's made of.

180050.Name: Gourmet Matcha Chocolate
180050.Desc: Matcha-flavored chocolate that Haruna made with Sensei to prove a theory about gourmet chocolate. You can taste the bitterness as well as the sweetness that comes from her grateful heart.

180051.Name: Skullman, the Valentine Saint
180051.Desc: A chocolate version of "Skullman, the Grim Reaper" prepared by Azusa. This is a limited-edition item that can only be obtained during the Valentine's Day season.

180052.Name: Lovely Cross Line
180052.Desc: Famous chocolate brought by Koharu. A premium mixture of white and dark chocolate, it's known for the cross in the center.

180053.Name: Twinkling Star
180053.Desc: Star-shaped chocolate that Suzumi bought at a convenience store. It is wrapped in gilt and shines brightly.

180054.Name: Chocolate Sister Figure
180054.Desc: A Sister figure gifted by Mari. It's made of chocolate. It may have been for display rather than for eating.

180055.Name: Bead Chocolate
180055.Desc: Special chocolate in the shape of beads so that chocolate doesn't get on your hands or leave crumbs. It is popular among avid readers, including Shimiko.

180056.Name: Be With You
180056.Desc: Serina's homemade chocolate. The sweet taste calms the heart.

180057.Name: Pennyroyal Chocolate Mint
180057.Desc: A specially-processed chocolate mint prepared by Airi. It's often gifted among enthusiasts due to its rarity.

180058.Name: Limited Yoshimi Edition
180058.Desc: Yoshimi's homemade chocolate. Can be considered a limited edition that cannot be seen anywhere else.

180059.Name: Chocolate Over Words
180059.Desc: Chocolate seemingly made by Natsu. It's a rather simple design and is intended to be a substitute for much of Natsu's speech.

180060.Name: Homemade Fortune Chocolate
180060.Desc: Fated chocolate that Chinatsu prepared. Various phrases are written inside.

180061.Name: Bandaged Chocolate
180061.Desc: Chocolate Sena made whenever she could find time while on call. She couldn't find any wrapping paper, so she wrapped it in a clean bandage instead.

180062.Name: Cacao 99.99%
180062.Desc: Very expensive chocolate Haruka bought for Sensei. You may be a good fit for Problem Solver 68 if the 99.99% cacao rating doesn't faze you.

180063.Name: Twisted Valentine
180063.Desc: Chocolate Asuna prepared for her master for Valentine's Day. It underwent a very minor modification during the making process.

180064.Name: Made By Maid
180064.Desc: Akane's homemade chocolate. The chocolate is very well made, showing off her skills as a maid.

180065.Name: Chocolate Omurice
180065.Desc: Omurice prepared by Karin for Valentine's Day. A heart is drawn on the omurice with chocolate instead of ketchup.

180066.Name: Chocolate Dragon Engraving
180066.Desc: A chocolate engraving of a dragon that Neru brought. There's no way to find out how or where she got it.

180067.Name: Valentine's Origins
180067.Desc: Chocolate made by Kotori to explain the origin and significance of Valentine's Day. Although it looks shabby, it tastes great.

180068.Name: Chocolate Sakazuki
180068.Desc: Chocolate in the shape of a drinking glass brought by Pina. Since it is a Valentine's Day souvenir, it is not actually a drinking glass, and you cannot fill it with alcohol.

180069.Name: Almond Crimson
180069.Desc: Chocolate-covered almonds left by Tsurugi. The glass bottle is tied with a cute red ribbon.

180070.Name: Messily Wrapped Chocolate
180070.Desc: Handmade chocolate wrapped clumsily by Kokona, though she'll never admit it was her handiwork. You'd better eat it alone, while no one's watching.

180071.Name: Chocolate Truffles for Children
180071.Desc: Chocolate truffles that Hinata keeps on hand to give to children who visit the cathedral. Hinata apparently knows the flavor of every type of truffle.

180072.Name: Squishy Chocolate Cookie
180072.Desc: Chocolate chip cookies made by Ui. She says that she used a recipe that doesn't leave crumbs.

180073.Name: Strawberry-Chocolate Cake
180073.Desc: A slice of chocolate cake topped with fresh strawberries. Kazusa spent a lot of time picking it out, so please respect that.

180074.Name: Small Wrapped Chocolate
180074.Desc: A small, neatly-wrapped Valentine chocolate. Hiyori says she's given up everything for it.

180075.Name: Thoroughly-Wrapped Chocolate
180075.Desc: An exceedingly well-wrapped Valentine chocolate. The complicated wrapper seems to reflect Misaki's personality.

180076.Name: Flowers and Chocolate
180076.Desc: Handmade chocolate and flowers personally grown by Atsuko. A princess is sure to have many secrets.

180077.Name: Decadent Chocolate
180077.Desc: The finest of chocolates prepared by Saori. Many happenings occurred behind the scenes in the process of their creation.

180078.Name: Cherry Blossom White Chocolate
180078.Desc: Mimori's special Cherry Blossom White Chocolate. They say Mimori pours her very heart into making it. As for the other rumor...it probably has nothing to do with mind reading. Probably.

180079.Name: Ultimate Chocosaur
180079.Desc: The ultimate chocosaur, created by Kaede. Unfortunately, she didn't manage to successfully "excavate" any of her fossil chocolates, but the experience inspired her. She combined the remaining pieces of chocolate together to create this. "It's the strongest dinosaur in history!" - Kaede.

180080.Name: Half-Melted Holland Lop Chocolate
180080.Desc: Tsukuyo's cute Holland Lop Rabbit character chocolate. She may have been holding it a bit too close, and the shape has changed a little...

180081.Name: Delicate Yet Beautiful Super Genius Hacker's Chocolate
180081.Desc: A chocolate made by Himari in her own image. After much logical deliberation, she made the rational decision that you needed to go back to Schale to eat it.

180082.Name: Iroha's Handmade Chocolate Breadsticks
180082.Desc: Handmade chocolate breadsticks made by Iroha. One of them has a small mark on it...

180083.Name: Ninjutsu Research Club Badge Chocolate Set
180083.Desc: A special chocolate custom-ordered by Michiru. She fumbled and stumbled her way through the gift-giving process, but her love for her classmates and her respect for Sensei couldn't be clearer.

180084.Name: Chocolate Carrot Cake
180084.Desc: Miyako baked this carrot cake with lots of chocolate. Aren't very sweet foods supposed to be bad for rabbits, though?

180085.Name: Chocolate S'mores
180085.Desc: Chocolate s'mores made by Moe. The calories in this sweet marshmallow and chocolate combo are...destructive.

180086.Name: Chocolate Caramel Ration
180086.Desc: A chocolate caramel ration that Saki gave you. It's popular among guards on duty at night who need help staying awake. Saki herself assured you many times that it has nothing to do with Valentine's Day.

180087.Name: Chocolate Bark
180087.Desc: A handmade chocolate bark from Miyu. She was supplied some chocolate and mixed it with fruit she gathered from the mountains. Why are the chocolate pieces all shaped like leaves, though?

180088.Name: Chocolate Ink
180088.Desc: Chocolate ink that Noa bought, possibly as a joke. It's not practical for writing, as it doesn't transfer well to quills and spoils easily, but it's perfect if you want to make a statement about your feelings.

180089.Name: Special Chocolate Medal of Merit
180089.Desc: A chocolate medal awarded to Marina for her contribution to the Cherenka. It's a testament to Marina's hard work and pride.

180090.Name: Shigure's Bittersweet Special
180090.Desc: A non-alcoholic chocolate cocktail mixed by Shigure. The trick is to add a square of bittersweet chocolate at the end for a clean, balanced taste.

180091.Name: Chick-Shaped Chocolate
180091.Desc: Chocolates that Mine swears are medical supplies. If this is medicine, it's strangely delicious, and the packaging is unusually cute.

180092.Name: Chocolate-Covered Grapefruit
180092.Desc: A snack Ayumu enjoys, chunks of dried grapefruit dipped in chocolate. Since it has caffeine, theobromine, and plenty of vitamins, it should help with feeling fatigued... Or something like that.

180093.Name: Homemade Chocolate Sticks
180093.Desc: Chocolate Ichika made for Sensei. It's shaped like a stick for convenient eating. Despite looking very amateurish, it appears and tastes just as good as a store-bought chocolate.

180094.Name: Chocolate Slipper
180094.Desc: A giant chocolate almost as big as a real slipper and much sturdier than it looks. You could probably even take a walk in it.

180095.Name: Secret Message
180095.Desc: A set of homemade chocolates Koyuki sent to Sensei. It might seem like a normal chocolate gift, but in true Koyuki fashion, it comes with a hidden message.

180096.Name: Self-Made Choice
180096.Desc: A premium chocolate set Sakurako got for Sensei. She painstakingly chose the best place to source this rare and valuable gift from.

180097.Name: Valentine Challenge
180097.Desc: Reisa's chocolate in the form of a letter. It's actually just a big piece of chocolate with an envelope on top. There must be a letter from Reisa inside...

180098.Name: Hot Springs Egg Chocolate
180098.Desc: Megu's special homemade chocolate. Despite the stark resemblance to hot springs eggs, don't get confused! She's made enough for everyone, so help yourself.

180099.Name: Chocolate Moon Cake
180099.Desc: Rumi made these chocolate moon cakes just for Sensei. Her immaculate skills are on display with the variety of styles and flavors.

180100.Name: Genryumon Pattern Chocolate
180100.Desc: A chocolate that Mina made based on her "most important thing." Her sentiment was clearly a good one, but it's hard to escape the feeling that something is amiss.

180101.Name: Chocolate Keychain
180101.Desc: A keychain and chocolate that Momiji claims she happened to win somewhere. Apparently by coincidence, Momiji has her own matching pair.

180102.Name: Nagisa's Simple Chocolate
180102.Desc: Nagisa's homemade chocolate, created with gratitude for Sensei. It's intentionally simple to avoid any kind of misunderstandings. However, the taste and quality of the chocolate far surpasses any store-bought product.

180103.Name: High-Calorie Chocolate
180103.Desc: Minori's solution to not being able to actually celebrate Valentine's day. While she claims she's giving it out of obligation, she actually put quite a bit of care into picking out the brand.

180104.Name: Different Perspectives
180104.Desc: A small box of chocolates Aoi made for Sensei. The diverse selection suggests Aoi painstakingly made each type to make sure she made at least one to Sensei's taste.

180105.Name: Plana-Full Chocolate
180105.Desc: A chocolate that Plana meticulously made without telling Arona. It tastes just the way Sensei likes it.

180106.Name: Self-Portrait Chocolate
180106.Desc: A piece of white chocolate featuring an image of Meru, by Meru. She seems concerned with the way it turned out, but the real concern seems to be where to start eating...

180107.Name: Best, Greatest, Ultimate Homemade Chocolate Cake
180107.Desc: Homemade chocolate cake that's claimed to rival that of the most famous bakery in Kivotos. Toki says her tagline for it is the best, greatest, ultimate.

180108.Name: Lead Strategist's Homemade Chocolate
180108.Desc: Homemade chocolate Kaho made for Sensei. At first glance, it looks like a simple promotional item, but each letter was carefully carved by hand with dedication and care.

180109.Name: An Everyday Coffee
180109.Desc: An average cup of joe Kanna made for Sensei. But rather unusually, it boasts a sweet, chocolate flavor, thanks perhaps to Kanna's brewing methods.

180110.Name: A Pair's Efforts: Raw Chocolate
180110.Desc: Renge's homemade raw chocolate, perfected with help from Sensei. Although clumsily made and not refined, the chocolates hold precious memories.

180111.Name: Operation Officer's Chocolate
180111.Desc: Chocolate Kikyou made for Sensei. It features a cute cat face that doesn't quite match its bland name. Maybe its hinting at a secret operation...or something?

180112.Name: Kadenokouji Amulet and Chocolate Stick
180112.Desc: Yukari went to the shopping district at the crack of dawn for this limited edition chocolate corn stick and paired it with a handmade amulet. This heartwarming gift is the embodiment of her passion as both a Kadenokouji and a Hyakkaryouran member.

180113.Name: Ibuki's Chocolate Pudding
180113.Desc: Chocolate pudding personally made by Ibuki herself. She might have put a little too much love into it, as it appears to be inundated with different toppings and sweets. Watch your sugar levels if you eat the whole thing!

180114.Name: Mika Special Chocolate Roll Cake ☆
180114.Desc: A chocolate roll cake Mika baked for Sensei. It's a bit clumsily made, but full of heart and a testament to Mika's hard work.

180115.Name: Chairman's Premium Chocolate Fountain
180115.Desc: A top-of-the-line chocolate fountain machine that Makoto had specially made for Sensei. She may have been a little overly ambitious with its features, however, as the various modifications caused it to start spraying chocolate every which way.

200000.Name: Phrenapates' Credit Card
200000.Desc: A credit card that was among Phrenapates' possessions. It's burnt so badly that it's almost unrecognizable and looks like it's about to crumble, so treat it carefully. You can use this card to obtain Pyroxenes, but once you do, it will be destroyed.

200001.Name: Credit Card Shards
200001.Desc: Remnants of Phrenapates' credit card. Very few people remember its original appearance.

20000000.Name: Arona's Stamp
20000000.Desc: A stamp of approval from Arona to Sensei!

20000001.Name: Video Game Magazine
20000001.Desc:
A magazine containing a scathing review of the Game Development Department's new video game.
All copies must be collected and destroyed at once!

20000002.Name: Perfect Exam Paper
20000002.Desc: An exam paper with a perfect score! Exemplary!

20000003.Name: Mission Report
20000003.Desc: A mission report detailing Schale activities.

20000004.Name: Marshmallow Skewer
20000004.Desc: Marshmallows on a wooden skewer. They're even sweeter when toasted over a bonfire.

20000005.Name: Old Arius Badge
20000005.Desc: An old commemorative badge. It displays the emblem of Arius Satellite School.

20000006.Name: Handmade Wreath
20000006.Desc: A beautiful wreath someone painstakingly made by hand.

20000007.Name: AMAS Debris
20000007.Desc: The broken debris of AMAS, the combat drone that guarded the Fortress City of Eridu.

20000008.Name: Film of Memories
20000008.Desc: A reel of film containing the last remaining traces of a teacher who walked alongside their students.

20000009.Name: Labor Party Flyer
20000009.Desc: A mysterious flyer that was issued by the Labor Party.

20000010.Name: Charcoal Chicken Skewers
20000010.Desc: Delicious chicken skewers grilled over fragrant charcoal.

20000011.Name: Shiba Seki Special Jumbo Ramen
20000011.Desc: Shiba Seki Ramen Shop's secret menu item that embodies Master Shiba's kindness.

20000012.Name: Abydos Student ID (First-year)
20000012.Desc: This first-year student ID proves you're a student at Abydos High School.

20001000.Desc: A stamp of approval from Arona to Sensei!

20001001.Name: Mug of Coffee
20001001.Desc: A mug of bitter black coffee to help fuel you during overtime.
